<body>
<div id="header"></div> 
    <div class="container mx-auto py-10 px-5">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto bg-white text-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden">
            <div class="p-4 sm:p-6">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-3xl text-center font-bold mb-10">Privacy Policy</h2>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">New Customer</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">The main purpose of the processing is the management of registered users on our website. Legitimation: Art. 6.1.a GDPR: explicit consent. The data will be kept until the user deletes their personal account.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Place or process an order</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">The data will be processed for the purpose of managing your purchase: shipping, collection, after-sales procedures. The legal basis for processing is the execution of the contractual relationship of sale in accordance with Art. 6.1.b) GDPR. The data may be communicated to the technical departments of manufacturers when necessary to process a product warranty. This communication is legitimized by Art. 6.1.c GDPR, as processing is necessary to fulfill the legal obligation of warranty stipulated by the Legislative Royal Decree 1/2007, of November 16, approving the revised text of the General Law for the Defense of Consumers and Users and other complementary laws. The data will be kept until the user deletes their personal account. Subsequently, they will be kept blocked until the date of prescription of legal actions (for example, legal warranty of the product or conservation of invoices). After this period, the data will be irreversibly deleted.</p>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mt-2">To process the delivery of your order, the delivery person may request identification data to identify you and prevent fraudulent deliveries (such as ID number, name, or surname). We inform you that your data will only be processed for this purpose. Under no circumstances will the delivery person be authorized to capture an image of your identification document, take photographs, or videos by any means.</p>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mt-2">If the collection is carried out by a person other than the one who processed the order, it is reported that the data processing is strictly necessary to prevent fraud in accordance with Consideration 47 GDPR. The legal basis legitimizing the processing is legitimate interest. The data will not be communicated to third parties, nor will it be subject to international transfer. The data will be kept during the verification period of the delivery and will subsequently be duly blocked for the period until the prescription date of legal actions. After this period, personal data will be irreversibly deleted. It is also reported that the image of your identification document can never be captured by the delivery person.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Newsletter and Advertising Delivery</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">When the user has not previously made a purchase at Customaize, only advertising related to our products and services will be sent if explicit consent is given for this purpose. The legitimizing basis is explicit consent in accordance with Art. 6.1.a GDPR. The data will be kept until the user expresses opposition to the processing through a simple and accessible unsubscribe procedure in each advertising communication.</p>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mt-2">People who have made purchases of products sold by Customaize may receive commercial communications based on Art. 21.2 of Law 34/2002, of July 11, on services of the information society and electronic commerce. The interested party may easily unsubscribe from the subscription through the link available in each communication.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Contests</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">The data will be processed to manage the participation of interested parties in the contest, as well as to communicate prizes to the winners. The legal basis legitimizing the processing is Art. 6.1.b GDPR, execution of the contractual relationship. The data will be kept until the prescription of legal actions, after which they will be deleted.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Contact Form</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">The data will be processed to manage the participation of interested parties in the contest, as well as to communicate prizes to the winners. The legal basis legitimizing the processing is Art. 6.1.b GDPR, execution of the contractual relationship. The data will be kept until the prescription of legal actions, after which they will be deleted.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Post a Review</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">It is reported that it is not necessary to use personal data to publish a review on the Customaize website. The interested party can choose an alias or pseudonym for this purpose. When the review contains personal data, the data will be processed for the purpose of publishing the review on the official Customaize website. The legal basis legitimizing the processing is Art. 6.1.a explicit consent. The data will be kept indefinitely as long as the review is published. If the interested party deletes the review, the data will be automatically deleted, unless they have violated our moderation policy available at Real Reviews from Real Customers (customaize.com). In this case, the data may be kept during the investigation and/or prescription period of legal actions.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Fulfillment</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Customaize provides logistical services to third-party sellers ("Sellers"). In this case, the Data Controller will be the Seller. However, to reinforce the principle of information, it is communicated that the data will be processed following, at all times, the instructions of the Seller. In any case, Customaize will keep the data solely and exclusively during the period of exercising the legal warranty of the product. Later, they will be deleted.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Repair Request Form</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">The data will be processed to issue a quote and manage the repair request. The legal basis for processing is Art. 6.1.a GDPR, the consent of the interested party. If the client accepts the repair quote, the legal basis will be Art. 6.1.c GDPR, execution of a contractual relationship. The data will be kept for the time necessary to provide the service. Subsequently, the data will be duly blocked during the prescription period of possible actions, and, after this period, completely deleted.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Chat</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">The data will be processed to process an information request made by the user. The legal basis for processing is Art. 6.1.b GDPR, the application at the request of the interested party for pre-contractual measures or the execution of the contractual relationship. The data will only be kept for the period necessary to process the query.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Recipients of the data</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-2">Due to the purchase, your data may be communicated to the following recipients:</p>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Banking entities for payment of purchases by card and/or study of financing purchases and obtaining consumer credits. The legal basis legitimizing the communication is Art. 6.1.b execution of the contractual relationship.
                    Entities providing fraud investigation, discovery, and prevention services, as well as minimizing the risk of their commission, based on the legitimate interest recognized by current regulations. The legal basis for the transfer is Art. 6.1.c legal obligation.
                    Entities and companies in the energy sector. The legal basis for the transfer is Art. 6.1.c legal obligation.
                    To the Office of Consumers and Users in case of any claim. The legal basis for the transfer is Art. 6.1.c legal obligation.
                    To manufacturers, technical services, and/or wholesalers in the case of warranties or repairs. To those transport companies that may be entrusted with shipping orders to customers. These recipients may be located within Spanish territory or outside it, depending on the product and/or service purchased. The legal basis legitimizing the communication is Art. 6.1.c legal obligation.
                    To companies providing transport and parcel shipping services. The legal basis for the transfer is Art. 6.1.b execution of the contractual relationship.
                    In cases legally established, such as the Forces and Security Forces. The legal basis for the transfer is Art. 6.1.c legal obligation.
                    To public administrations to which we have to provide information at the request of a requirement. The legal basis for the transfer is Art. 6.1.c legal obligation.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Rights of interested parties</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-2">The interested party can exercise the following rights.</p>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">They may request information about the personal data stored that concern them (access).
                    They may request the correction of the inaccuracy of their personal data (rectification).
                    They may request the deletion or limitation of the processing of their personal data (deletion and limitation).
                    They may also request that their personal data be made available to them in a structured, common, and machine-readable format (portability).Opposition to processing, for example, against receiving advertising (opposition).</p>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mt-2 mb-2">To do this, they can exercise their rights in writing by sending an email to the address: lopd@customaize.com. If Customaize has reasonable doubts about the identity of the individual making the request, they may ask for additional information necessary to confirm the identity of the interested party.</p>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mt-2 mb-2">The interested party also has the right to file a complaint with the data protection authorities (Spanish Data Protection Agency). However, for any issues related to data, we invite you to contact us to resolve them.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Data Protection Officer</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">We have appointed a Data Protection Officer (DPO) for any issues related to your personal data. You can contact them at the address lopd@customaize.com.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Data Quality</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Users must ensure the truthfulness, accuracy, authenticity, and currency of the personal data collected.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Protection of Minors</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">We do not collect personal data from minors. It is the responsibility of the parent/guardian to ensure the privacy of minors, doing everything possible to ensure that they have authorized the collection and use of the minor's personal data.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-2 mb-2">Social Networks</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Through our website, you can access open-access social networks such as Facebook, Twitter, TikTok, or Youtube. These are websites where users can register and follow us for free. On these social networks, users can learn about our activities, opinions, access photos, and videos. Users of these social networks should be aware that this place is independent of the website www.Customaize.com and is open, meaning it is visible to all its users. The privacy policies applicable to these contents are those established by each social network. Customaize is not the owner of social networks.</p>
                    <p class="text-1xl font-semibold leading-relaxed mt-12 mb-2">Updated: March 13, 2024</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</html>
